OL,3,CCountry park loses over 100 trees to
OL,4,Cstorm as pictures show scale of damage
OL,6,F"This comes on the heels of Storm
OL,7,FBert, just two weeks ago, which caused
OL,8,Fextensive destruction, including the
OL,9,Floss of several bridges and widespread
OL,10,Ffootpath damage. Our wardens are
OL,11,Fcurrently prioritising clearing
OL,12,Fblocked paths, repairing
OL,13,Finfrastructure, and making the wider
OL,14,Fpark safe for visitors."
OL,16,FCraig y Nos Country Park manager Paul
OL,17,FChapman said: "The scale of the damage
OL,18,Fcaused by Storm Darragh is truly
OL,19,Fdevastating, particularly so soon
OL,20,Fafter Storm Bert.
